column5: First light atop Twin Peaks, first time trying San Bruno Mountain. Exhausting, with some bonks here and there. But great views and a fun challenge.

Longer than 25 miles & probably another 400 feet of elevation as I hit pause on Strava atop Twin Peaks & didnt turn back on until back in GG Park after heading back down Portola & taking 20th Ave to GG Park. But a gorgeous morning to be out, even with 2 close calls on getting doored & a near-mishap with an oblivious dude jogging in a bike lane w/ a dog on a long lead who almost clotheslined me. Felt lucky to get back with no broken bones.

column5: Last ride in SF, time to find new  adventures in . But a lovely spin thru the usual routewiggle, panhandle, GG Park, Great (Sandy) Highway, Sloat, Lake Merced, Portola & Twin Peaks. Sadly Strava didnt do the usual auto resume after my brief stop at OB, so best guess is about 21 miles with 1500 foot elevation gain. Au revoir SF, it was fun seeing you on two wheels.
